				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">MMC6 is just MMC3 with a particular method of PRG RAM enabling. It can be distinguished from MMC3 in NES 2.0 based on PRG RAM size. Likewise, the only difference between NROM and the PA10/PA11 variant of this poor man's OneBus is 1. the CHR holes are unpopulated and 2. CIRAM /CE is grounded. That's why I favor making the PA10/PA11 variant a variant of #0 distinguished by NES 2.0's CHR RAM size field being 0.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

