				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">How about using <strong>BNROM</strong> for the horizontal/vertical mirroring variants and <strong>AxROM</strong> for the single screen variants? iNES 2.0 submapper codes would indicate that the ROM actually belongs in this single chip cart, but emulators not aware of this cart or even iNES 2.0 would still run the games (as long as the programmer didn't abuse the mirroring, in which case an emulator aware of the single chip cart would have to be used). This is the cleanest solution I can think of.<br /><br />EDIT: Well, there's still the problem that the iNES header doesn't allow the selection of which name table to use with single screen mirroring on AxROM, since this is controlled by the mapper. Would repurposing the H/V bit (which would only work on emulators aware of the single chip cart, to be compatible with AxROM the game would have to perform a mapper write to select a name table) be as frowned upon as repurposing the 4-screen bit like nocash suggested?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

